revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use}}
{{Lua|Module:Infobox dim}}
<!-- Categories and interwikis go at the bottom of this page. -->

== Usage ==
{{tl|Infobox dim}} is used inside infoboxes to generate the dim argument for geohack links. The template accepts a number of (optional) parameters that describe the physical dimensions of an object:
{{div col|colwidth=15em}}
* length_mi
* length_km
* width_mi
* width_km
* area_mi2
* area_km2
* area_acre
* area_ha
{{div col end}}
The template also accepts other geohack parameters to generate the dim argument:
* scale
* type (e.g., "mountain" or "city")
* population (for type="city" only)

== See also ==
*{{tl|Infobox mountain}}
*{{tl|Infobox ecoregion}}
*{{tl|Infobox protected area}}
<includeonly>
<!-- Categories and interwikis go here: -->
{{Sandbox other||
[[Category:Map formatting and function templates]]
[[Category:Place-related infobox templates]]
}}
</includeonly>

